<br>
As for kids, all media is full of literature not suited for everyone--literature, movies, you name it.  Why should video games be restricted more heavilly?  It is a form of media after all.  Sure, it should be kept away from kids without proper guidance if it contains certain material just like movies are.  That's been done with the ratings.  The rest is up to people to actually check the ratings before they let their kids play.  I remember I wasn't allowed to play Mortal Kombat and other violent games when I was younger :P  My mom didn't need a sticker, she just took a hint that mangling bodies wasn't wholesome entertainment for a child.  Imagine that.  And it didn't keep me from being any more messed up if you ask me.  Some people are just going to be messed up. <p><a href="http://magitek.nu/moonpie" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.tbns.net/sistaninja/turkbanner2.jpg" border="0"></a>
