there's been dozens of cases where people have sued over stuff like that. lawn mowers tend to have stickers on them that warn they shouldn't be used as hedge trimmers 'cause some guy picked one up by the sides thinking he'd trim the bushes with it and chopped his fingers off. <br>
those cases are a little different than the video game thing though. yeah the guy was being an idiot to pick up the lawn mower but some people simply don't think of things like that. <br>
this guy who commited suicide was obviously already disturbed. i don't think the game had any direct influence on his decision to kill himself and i don't think that games should have warning labels on them (aside from the already existing age ratings.) as i mentioned earlier i don't think games or movies make people go out and kill other people, but i think they do have some affect on us. that's what always bugs me is that some crazy goes and shoots himself in the head after spending three weeks playing some game and half the people say &quot;oh, the game made him do it&quot; and the other half say &quot;games don't affect anyone like that.&quot; neither one is true. <br>
anyway, i'm ranting again. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
